s of modern American literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aAuthors and readerszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAuthors, AmericanxBiographyxHistory and criticism. 0aAuthorshipxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAutobiography. 0aCanon (Literature). 0aCelebritieszUnited StatesvBiographyxBiographyxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and societyzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiteraturexAppreciationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479891825.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479891825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479891825/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles